🧵Lying down slows my heart, breathing gets heavy then finally "normal". Gotta take more meds by this point as the pain is back. More meds means more sleepy me. I took prescription iron pill this morning, still sleepy tho. Can't win. #NEISvoid

🧵I lean back to rest my eyes & try to relax for a min. Next thing I know it's 6pm & I'm in agony again. What happened!? That's it, my assignment is late & my head is fuzzy all over again. I need to lie down. Every muscle in my body has tremors & pain. HR is high again. #NEISvoid

🧵Food in, I can take my meds. These are the same painkillers given to cancer patients. Add daily puffs of 2 inhalers. Fully intending on getting uni assignment done, laptop on knee. Meds have kicked in, heart rate still at 155, feel like I'm having a heart attack #NEISvoid

🧵Eventually got up, had to get help to get dressed. Have to hold onto the wall & banister to slowly get down the stairs. Hubby makes food coz I can't stand up for long. Sitting watching TV & heart rate was at 155bpm. This is exhausting. #NEISvoid
